==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Narrow-minded
<hw>Nar"row-mind`ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of narrow
mental scope; lacking tolerance or breadth of view; illiberal; mean.
Opposite of <ant>broad-minded</ant>, <ant>open-minded</ant>,
<ant>liberal</ant>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns> [Narrower terms:
<stype>dogmatic, dogmatical</stype>; <stype>little, petty, small,
small-minded</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> narrowminded, narrow, illiberal,
intolerant.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Capable of being shocked by behavior of others.
Opposite of <ant>unshockable</ant>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> shockable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p> -- <wordforms><wf>Nar"row-mind`ed*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Narrowness</ent>⟦br⟧
